          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2022-07-29 14:59:23.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThanks Francesco, and Liam for the feedback.  I guess I am having a little trouble seeing the degree of automation vs disruption tradeoffs introduced.   For example it would be nice to see an example on how it works and the code impacts and maintenance moving forward that introduces.   On the other side of the tradeoffs, the PAP is a mature project with over 93% code coverage, and with little REST API changes I would expect in the near future.   I realize that some less mature components may benefit more from this approach that the PAP, perhaps the ACM where I would expect more REST API churn there.   What are your thoughts on this?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "a233021c531ee2cbb79545fc0abfa86e6b379040",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2787,
          "name": "Liam Fallon",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
          "username": "liamfallon"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2022-07-29 15:41:25.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> Thanks Francesco, and Liam for the feedback.  I guess I am having a little trouble seeing the degree of automation vs disruption tradeoffs introduced.   For example it would be nice to see an example on how it works and the code impacts and maintenance moving forward that introduces.   On the other side of the tradeoffs, the PAP is a mature project with over 93% code coverage, and with little REST API changes I would expect in the near future.   I realize that some less mature components may benefit more from this approach that the PAP, perhaps the ACM where I would expect more REST API churn there.   What are your thoughts on this?\n\nMaybe we should put this as work in progress for now and discuss further after the vacation period?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
